<p>Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro has asked Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes to let him serve his 27-year sentence under house arrest, citing health concerns [straitstimes.com#1][aljazeera.com#1]. The sentence is tied to allegations he fomented a coup after his 2022 election defeat, which he is seeking to appeal [aljazeera.com#1]. His lawyers cite recent medical issues, including a September skin cancer diagnosis and a hospital visit in Brasília for violent hiccups, vomiting, and low blood pressure [firstpost.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/4bgRuqrk7rLAYB6l_966fBR-Yz_LmkzpM0V4XGOW2jQNHMenIUuAJWjSmYTMvKuEP7mSifgTv-5dIUzmb262tJAH9Ux73bYm5xC_3j4VJMfHDZejY4rB4N7wZ1wJ2CctBtweYrbs4qaqHrUbEXU8gGpVsu4do4sJXIAFQ1aRwXm5uaFOxs2DSFoQzMH_b1L_kED2' alt='Former Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro, whose lawyers request house arrest on health grounds.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>House arrest request: Bolsonaro’s legal team petitioned Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes to allow him to serve his 27-year term at home due to health reasons [straitstimes.com#1][aljazeera.com#1]</li><li>Appeal underway: He has sought to appeal the conviction tied to claims he fomented a coup following his 2022 electoral loss [aljazeera.com#1]</li><li>Health grounds: His defense cites a September skin cancer diagnosis and a recent hospital episode in Brasília involving violent hiccups, vomiting, and low blood pressure while under guard [firstpost.com#1]</li><li>Judicial next steps: The decision on detention conditions rests with Justice de Moraes of Brazil’s Supreme Court [straitstimes.com#1]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Bolsonaro’s defense team: They argue his medical condition warrants house arrest rather than prison custody [firstpost.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/bolsonaros-lawyer-seek-house-arrest-for-former-prez-over-health-concerns-13952985.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Brazilian Supreme Court (Justice Alexandre de Moraes): He is being asked to decide whether Bolsonaro may serve his sentence at home [straitstimes.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/bolsonaro-lawyers-seek-house-arrest-for-coup-plot-sentence'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Al Jazeera reporting: Reports that Bolsonaro is appealing a 27-year sentence linked to allegations he fomented a coup after the 2022 election [aljazeera.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/21/former-president-jair-bolsonaro-asks-to-serve-house-arrest-in-brazil'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/bolsonaro-lawyers-seek-house-arrest-for-coup-plot-sentence'>Bolsonaro lawyers seek house arrest for coup plot sentence</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/11/21/former-president-jair-bolsonaro-asks-to-serve-house-arrest-in-brazil'>Former President Jair Bolsonaro asks to serve house arrest in Brazil</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/bolsonaros-lawyer-seek-house-arrest-for-former-prez-over-health-concerns-13952985.html'>Bolsonaro&#x27;s lawyer seek house arrest for former prez over health concerns</a> - firstpost.com</li></ul>